      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The same sort of overzealous valuations were at play during the 2000s housing bubble, and they could once again lead to catastrophe. We‚Äôve already seen the first signs of trouble: Last year, the mammoth California Public Employees' Retirement System unloaded a $6 billion private equity portfolio at a ",
